text: Well, I'm just speaking from my own experience, but cEDH peeps usually play with their own to avoid pubstomping.

For some they brew competitive decks to pubstomp, but I think the vast majority of cEDH players are min-maxers who really want to push the limits of the format, even if there are only a handful of real top-tier win-cons.

If you watch or read content done by the Lab Maniacs, it's clear that they're passionate about the format as a way to test their playing and deckbuilding skills against other like-minded players, and not to grind casual players into dust.
For sure, they do good stuff, and their interest in indeed cEDH. I just think there's a lot more pubstompers in the wild than most cEDH players want to admit
r/CompetitiveEDH is also full of really interesting discussion that can find application in casual EDH.
Maybe that's true. Just hasn't been my experience.
The most salt I witness is at casual pods on EDH night.

Because I don't have the budget to play cEDH at the highest tier - my Marwyn is tier 2.5 at best - I sometimes hop on Cockatrice to play or watch a cEDH game. Very amicable atmosphere, even if the tension is through the roof.
When I play "casual" EDH on Cockatrice though... woah Nelly.
Rage train to QQ town.
Im in the category of aggressive min/maxers that strive to stay casual
I literally built a service to help me minmax
Yep I feel it. I just think cEDH is a legitimate format and community that perhaps has different goals and ideals, but nonetheless respectable. And I would say the same about the non-cEDH crowd.
When the two sides mix and there's a failure of communication, things get messy, egos get bruised, and so on, but I think communicating well can fix all that.
Anyway, I don't wanna play Vector Asp in Lazav lol...
I'd rather just run Tainted Strike or Grafted Exo I think.
I just want to play [[Thief of Sanity]] as my commander, and Lazav makes that possible.

text: I think there are two different kinds of salt. When I see someone butt hurt at a casual table it’s almost always someone just bad at controlling their emotions, personal interaction etc. when I have a bad experience w a cEDH game it’s because someone is intentionally a malicious asshole
I’m way more forgiving of someone having an off night than someone doing a search for best flash Hulk combo so they can shit on someone playing gorgon tribal
That’s certainly not all or even most cEDH players but that element exists in a way unique to the format
And that sucks for guys like Lab Maniacs having to deal w that association
What about Himalayan salt? Does that count too?

It’s all about social tact, honestly.
There was a great thread relating to that on the EDH subreddit recently.
People need to recognize the environment and communicate expectations and adjust accordingly. If you’re the sole person trying to start an arms race, don’t. It just creates a warping effect.
Power level should meet power level.

But, unfortunately, that doesn’t happen. I know plenty of people who, while not magic players, enjoy “stomping competition” in certain scenarios. Those people do exist, and they will always bend towards cEDH to get their thrills, which, obviously garners infamy for the format itself.
Plus, it’s not so hard to carry multiple decks. If you can afford a cEDH deck, you can afford to bring a more casual deck. Anything else is just a pathetic excuse.

More I play the more I realize it's more the inherent desire to win that's to blame more than anything else. I try giving benefit of the doubt on that with various excuses, such as people have different opinions of power level... but the same people I see freaking out in cedh are the same ones freaking out in casual. Looking at it this way (and those social ticks some people have) it makes it all alot clearer for me lol. People get salty for losing or people dont want to lose so they stomp on purpose. Every other explanation just adds another needless layer for me. Just got to get lucky and find those people whose purpose of playing is far beyond the main objective of the game itself, like socializing or doing neat/silly things.
I mean you could also find a group of people who take losing as it's nothing, but that's the most mythical unicorn of all....
